verses.verse: Praise <WH1984> the Lord! <WH3050> Praise, <WH1984> O servants <WH5650> of the Lord. <WH3068> Praise <WH1984> the name <WH8034> of the Lord. <WH3068>
Blessed <WH1288> be the name <WH8034> of the Lord <WH3068> From this <WH6258> time <WH6258> forth and forever. <WH5704> <WH5769>
From the rising <WH4217> of the sun <WH8121> to its setting <WH3996> The name <WH8034> of the Lord <WH3068> is to be praised. <WH1984>
The Lord <WH3068> is high <WH7311> above <WH5921> all <WH3605> nations; <WH1471> His glory <WH9202> is above <WH5921> the heavens. <WH8064>
Who <WH4310> is like the Lord <WH3068> our God, <WH430> Who is enthroned <WH3427> on high, <WH1361>
Who humbles <WH8213> Himself to behold <WH7200> [The things that are] in heaven <WH8064> and in the earth <WH776>?
He raises <WH6965> the poor <WH1800> from the dust, <WH6083> And lifts <WH7311> the needy <WH34> from the ash <WH830> heap, <WH6083>
To make [them] sit <WH3427> with princes, <WH5081> With the princes <WH5081> of His people. <WH5971>
He makes the barren <WH6135> woman <WH6135> abide <WH3427> in the house <WH1004> [As] a joyful <WH8056> mother <WH517> of children. <WH1121> Praise <WH1984> the Lord! <WH3050>
